{"nodes":[{"content":"ms.ContentId: A6DD6776-614C-4D28-9B83-CB2EDFD263A3","pos":[0,50]},{"content":"title: Step 2: Install Hyper-V on Windows 10","pos":[51,95]},{"content":"Step 2: Install Hyper-V on Windows 10","pos":[99,136]},{"content":"12-Nov update.","pos":[138,152]},{"content":"Before you can begin using virtual machines on Windows 10 you will need to enable the Hyper-V role.","pos":[153,252]},{"content":"This can be done using the Windows 10 graphical user interface, PowerShell or DISM.","pos":[253,336]},{"content":"This documents will walk through each of these.","pos":[337,384]},{"content":"Enable Hyper-V Through the GUI","pos":[389,419]},{"content":"Right click on the Windows button and select ‘Programs and Features’.","pos":[424,493]},{"content":"Select ‘Turn Windows Features on or off’.","pos":[498,539]},{"content":"Select ‘Hyper-V’ and click ‘OK’.","pos":[544,576]},{"content":"When the installation has completed you will be prompted to restart your computer.","pos":[620,702]},{"content":"Enable Hyper-V with PowerShell","pos":[742,772]},{"content":"Open a PowerShell console as Administrator.","pos":[777,820]},{"content":"Enter the following command:","pos":[825,853]},{"content":"```Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Hyper-V –All`","pos":[855,932]},{"content":"When the installation has completed you will need to reboot the computer.","pos":[934,1007]},{"content":"Enable Hyper-V with DISM.","pos":[1012,1037]},{"content":"The Deployment Image Servicing and Management tool or DISM is used to service Windows images and prepare Windows Pre installation Evironments.","pos":[1039,1181]},{"content":"DISM can also be used to enable Windows features in running instances of the OS.","pos":[1182,1262]},{"content":"To enable the Hyper-V role using DISM:","pos":[1264,1302]},{"content":"Open up a PowerShell or CMD session as Administrator.","pos":[1307,1360]},{"content":"Type the following command:","pos":[1365,1392]},{"content":"Once completed you will be prompted to reboot.","pos":[1466,1512]},{"content":"Next Step","pos":[1543,1552]},{"content":"Step 3: Create a virtual switch","pos":[1555,1586]}],"content":"ms.ContentId: A6DD6776-614C-4D28-9B83-CB2EDFD263A3\ntitle: Step 2: Install Hyper-V on Windows 10\n\n# Step 2: Install Hyper-V on Windows 10\n\n12-Nov update. Before you can begin using virtual machines on Windows 10 you will need to enable the Hyper-V role. This can be done using the Windows 10 graphical user interface, PowerShell or DISM. This documents will walk through each of these.\n\n## Enable Hyper-V Through the GUI\n\n1. Right click on the Windows button and select ‘Programs and Features’.\n\n2. Select ‘Turn Windows Features on or off’.\n\n3. Select ‘Hyper-V’ and click ‘OK’.  \n<br />![](media/enable_role_upd.png)\n\n4. When the installation has completed you will be prompted to restart your computer.  \n<br />![](media/restart_upd.png)\n\n## Enable Hyper-V with PowerShell\n\n1. Open a PowerShell console as Administrator.\n\n2. Enter the following command:\n\n```Enable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName Microsoft-Hyper-V –All`\n\nWhen the installation has completed you will need to reboot the computer.\n\n## Enable Hyper-V with DISM.\n\nThe Deployment Image Servicing and Management tool or DISM is used to service Windows images and prepare Windows Pre installation Evironments. DISM can also be used to enable Windows features in running instances of the OS.\n\nTo enable the Hyper-V role using DISM:\n\n1. Open up a PowerShell or CMD session as Administrator.\n\n2. Type the following command:\n\n```DISM /Online /Enable-Feature /All /FeatureName:Microsoft-Hyper-V```\n\nOnce completed you will be prompted to reboot.\n\n![](media/dism_upd.png)\n\n\n## Next Step \n[Step 3: Create a virtual switch](walkthrough_virtual_switch.md) \n"}